### Problem

### Summary

After updating to Flutter **3.35.3** (Dart **3.9.2**), I started encountering persistent LSP errors from the Dart language server (`dartls`) when editing Dart files in Neovim using the built-in LSP client.

The errors appear when:
- Creating a new Dart file and typing (triggering LSP snippet completions),
- Editing an existing file near the end (triggering LSP snippet completions).

```
LSP[dartls] An error occurred while handling textDocument/didChange notification
```

This happens even in a minimal Neovim setup using only `nvim-lspconfig`.

[Original issue in dart sdk repo](https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/issues/61488)

CC: @DanTup (Dart LSP developer who helped analyze this)

---

### Steps to Reproduce

1. `flutter create test_did_change`
2. Open `test_did_change/lib/main.dart`
3. Begin typing at the end of the file to trigger the LSP snippet completion
4. Create a new file `named new_file.dart`
5. Begin typing in `new_file.dart` to trigger the LSP snippet completion

---

### Observed Behavior

The Dart LSP server logs errors during the `textDocument/didChange` notification. Based on analysis from the Dart LSP developer, Neovim's LSP client is sending malformed `didChange` notifications with incorrect text ranges.

Examples of invalid behavior:

[dart-lsp-log.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/22331971/dart-lsp-log.txt)

#### Insertions Treated Sequentially (Snippet Completion)
```json
{
  "text": "C",
  "range": { "start": { "line": 123, "character": 6 }, "end": { "line": 123, "character": 6 } }
},
{
  "text": "l",
  "range": { "start": { "line": 123, "character": 7 }, "end": { "line": 123, "character": 7 } }
},
...
```
Each character is inserted at a new offset, as if earlier insertions had already modified the buffer. But LSP spec requires all edits in a single `didChange` to apply to the original state of the document.

### Relevant LSP Specification

> When a client sends a `textDocument/didChange` notification, the ranges in `contentChanges` must all reference the same version of the document (before any of the edits are applied). Applying the changes in any order should result in the same document state.

See: [microsoft/language-server-protocol#888](https://github.com/microsoft/language-server-protocol/issues/888)

---

### Test Environment

- NVIM v0.11.4
  - Build type: RelWithDebInfo
  - LuaJIT 2.1.1753364724
- Flutter SDK: 3.35.3 (Dart 3.9.2)
- LSP Client: Built-in `vim.lsp`, configured via `nvim-lspconfig`
```lua
        dartls = {
          cmd = { "dart", "language-server", "--protocol=lsp" },
          filetypes = { "dart" },
          root_markers = { 'pubspec.yaml' },
          init_options = {
            onlyAnalyzeProjectsWithOpenFiles = true,
            suggestFromUnimportedLibraries = false,
            closingLabels = true,
            outline = true,
            flutterOutline = true,
          },
          settings = {
            dart = {
              analysisExcludedFolders = {
                vim.fn.expand("$PUB_CACHE"),
                vim.fn.expand("$FLUTTER_ROOT"),
                vim.fn.expand("$XDG_DATA_HOME/dart"),
                vim.fn.expand("$XDG_CACHE_HOME/dart"),
              },
              updateImportsOnRename = true,
              completeFunctionCalls = true,
              showTodos = true,
            },
          },
          capabilities = require("cmp_nvim_lsp").default_capabilities()
        },

```

### Code example

<details>
<summary>main.dart</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  // This widget is the root of your application.
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Flutter Demo',
      theme: ThemeData(
        colorScheme: ColorScheme.fromSeed(seedColor: Colors.deepPurple),
      ),
      home: const MyHomePage(title: 'Flutter Demo Home Page'),
    );
  }
}

class MyHomePage extends StatefulWidget {
  const MyHomePage({super.key, required this.title});

  final String title;

  @override
  State<MyHomePage> createState() => _MyHomePageState();
}

class _MyHomePageState extends State<MyHomePage> {
  int _counter = 0;

  void _incrementCounter() {
    setState(() {
      _counter++;
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        backgroundColor: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.inversePrimary,
        title: Text(widget.title),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Column(
          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
          children: <Widget>[
            const Text('You have pushed the button this many times:'),
            Text(
              '$_counter',
              style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineMedium,
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
      floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton(
        onPressed: _incrementCounter,
        tooltip: 'Increment',
        child: const Icon(Icons.add),
      ), // This trailing comma makes auto-formatting nicer for build methods.
    );
  }
}

class NewClassAtTheEndOfTheFile{

}
```
</details>

<details>
<summary>new_file.dart</summary>

```dart
class NewClassInTheNewFile{

}
``` 
</details>

---

Please let me know if I can help provide logs, a reproducible config.



### Steps to reproduce using "nvim -u minimal_init.lua"

```lua
local pattern = 'dart'
local cmd = { "dart", "language-server", "--protocol=lsp" }
-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project
local root_markers = { 'pubspec.yaml' }
-- Change to table with settings if required
local settings = vim.empty_dict()

vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {
  pattern = pattern,
  callback = function(args)
    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]
    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil
    vim.lsp.start({
      name = 'bugged-ls',
      cmd = cmd,
      root_dir = root_dir,
      settings = settings
    })
  end
})
```

### Expected behavior

The client should:
- Accumulate multiple text edits targeting the same document version,
- Ensure all ranges are calculated based on the unmodified buffer,
- Send a single `didChange` notification with all `contentChanges` referencing the original state.

### Nvim version (nvim -v)

v0.11.4

### Language server name/version

Dart **3.9.2**

### Operating system/version

Linux arch 6.16.5-arch1-1

### Log file

https://github.com/user-attachments/files/22331971/dart-lsp-log.txt

